This NLP project classifies text into emotional categories (like joy, sadness, anger, etc.) using a TF-IDF-based pipeline and a tuned logistic regression model.

 Dataset
Source: Emotion Dataset (train, val, test split)

Format: Each line â†’ text ; label

Emotions include: joy, anger, sadness, fear, love, surprise

 Pipeline
Label Encoding: Converts emotion strings to numbers

TF-IDF Vectorization: Transforms text into numerical features

MaxAbsScaler: Scales sparse data while preserving sparsity

Model: LogisticRegression with GridSearchCV over:

C: [0.1, 1, 10]

solver: ['liblinear', 'saga']

penalty: ['l1', 'l2']
  Accuracy: 0.9020
 Precision: 0.9011
 Recall: 0.9020
 F1 Score: 0.9013
 MSE: 0.6310
